What: Java Inner Class or nested class are declared inside class or interface

Why: They are used for grouping classes and interface at one place. So it will be easy to maintain 
     and readable. Get access to outer class private member and methods.
     
   There are two types
   a: Static nested class
   b: Non Static nested class
   
   
   Non static method can be categorized
   a: Member inner class
   b: Anonymous inner class
   c: Local inner class
   
   Member inner class: A class defined outside method and inside class. 
  
   Anonymous inner class: A class created for implementing interface or extending class. Name of class is defined
                         by java compiler.
   
   Local inner class: A class is created inside method.   
   
   Static nested class : A static class created within class.                   